headline: Morgan Stanley (NYSE:MS) Reports Impressive US$3,714 Million Earnings As Stock Dips 7%
summary: Morgan Stanley (NYSE:MS) recently declared regular dividends on its preferred stock, yet over the last quarter, the company's share price experienced a 7% decline. This negative price move occurred amid efforts to offload substantial debt related to Elon Musk's acquisition, a strategic decision reflecting shifts in the company’s loan portfolio. Despite an impressive increase in fourth-quarter earnings, which saw net income rise to $3,714 million, the share buyback program and the appointment...
